          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is not the same as buying a brand new Chevy Corvette or Porsche 911. After all, there’s no factory warranty and information about some cars can be scarce. For people who grew up around older cars, this is familiar ground. But if you’re unfamiliar with classic cars, the potential pitfalls aren’t clear, making the experience far more frightening. Before you just take the plunge blindly, following are some classic car buying tips from the experts at ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Farland Classic Car Restoration",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
